"{\"uid\": \"theyucatantimes.com-2024-08-climber-who-tried-to-scale-eiffel-tower-on-last-day-of-paris-olympics-gets-arrested\", \"text\": \"  A climber scaled the north face of the Eiffel Tower in Paris on Sunday, the last day of the Olympics, before he was intercepted by police mid-way up, police said.  \\\"At 2.45 pm, an individual was seen climbing the Eiffel Tower. The police immediately intervened and arrested the individual,\\\" a police spokesman said.  Item 1 of 4 A man climbs the Eiffel Tower on the Olympics' last day, August 11, 2024, in this screen grab taken from a video. KEVIN WINSTON/via REUTERS  [1/4]A man climbs the Eiffel Tower on the Olympics' last day, August 11, 2024, in this screen grab taken from a video. KEVIN WINSTON/via REUTERS\\u00a0Purchase Licensing\\u00a0Rightsopens new tab  Videos posted on social media showed the bare-chested climber skirting the Olympic rings as he made his way up without ropes. In one, the grinning climber can be heard saying to bystanders \\\"Bloody warm, innit?\\\" as he is escorted off the viewing platform by police.  The tower operator did not respond to a request for comment by REUTERS.  TYT Newsroom      The Yucat\\u00e1n Times is the herald of the Yucat\\u00e1n Peninsula, a vibrant chronicle that weaves the pulse of ancient traditions with the modern spirit of Mexico's southeastern jewel.  This website uses cookies to improve your experience. We will assume you are ok with this, but you can opt-out if you wish.Accept\"}"